  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "15, 16. we took up our carriages—\"our baggage.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and went up to Jerusalem—for the fifth time after his conversion, thus concluding his third missionary tour, which proved his last, so far as recorded; for though he accomplished the fourth and last part of the missionary plan sketched out (Ac 19:21)—\"After I have been at Jerusalem, I must also see Rome\"—it was as \"a prisoner of Jesus Christ.\"",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
